nge — the research and write-tests phases remain as-is. The SKILL.md orchestrator also stays the same since it just delegates to the procedure files.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`** — Complete rewrite of the procedure\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nReplace the current unit-test-first TDD cycles (Steps 4-9) with an E2E-test-driven progression:\\n\\n### New implementer.md Structure\\n\\n**Steps 1-2: Unchanged** — Read implementation guide + reference implementation (these provide essential context)\\n\\n**Step 3: Create bare-minimum package that compiles** — All interface methods as stubs. Wire up blank imports in `hooks_cmd.go` and `config.go`. Run `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test` to verify compilation.\\n\\n**Step 4: E2E Tier 1 — `TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits`** — No agent prompt needed. Requires real `InstallHooks()`, basic `ParseHookEvent()`, `AreHooksInstalled()`. After passing, write `hooks_test.go` and initial `lifecycle_test.go` unit tests.\\n\\n**Step 5: E2E Tier 2 — `TestSingleSessionManualCommit`** — The foundational test. Requires complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all 4 basic events, real `GetSessionDir`/`ResolveSessionFile`/`ReadTranscript`/`ChunkTranscript`/`ReassembleTranscript`, and `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods. After passing, write `types_test.go`, full `lifecycle_test.go`, and `transcript_test.go`.\\n\\n**Step 6: E2E Tier 2b — `TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation`** — Validates transcript quality (JSONL validity, content hash, prompts). May expose bugs in transcript formatting.\\n\\n**Step 7: E2E Tier 3 — `TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn`** — Agent creates + commits in one prompt. Tests in-turn commit path. Usually no new agent code needed.\\n\\n**Step 8: E2E Tier 4 — Multi-session tests** — `TestMultiSessionManualCommit`, `TestMultiSessionSequential`, `TestEndedSessionUserCommitsAfterExit`.\\n\\n**Step 9: E2E Tier 5 — Edge cases** — `TestModifyExistingTrackedFile`, `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges`, `TestDeletedFilesCommitDeletion`, etc.\\n\\n**Step 10: Optional interfaces** — `TranscriptPreparer`, `TokenCalculator`, `SubagentAwareExtractor` based on research feasibility.\\n\\n**Step 11: E2E Tier 6 — Interactive + rewind tests** — If agent supports interactive mode.\\n\\n**Step 12: E2E Tier 7 — Complex scenarios** — Stash workflows, rapid commits, subagent flows.\\n\\n**Steps 13-14: Register/wire up + final validation** — Same as current.\\n\\n### Key Principles Embedded in Each Step\\n\\nEach E2E tier follows the same cycle:\\n1. **Run the E2E test** — `mise run test:e2e:$AGENT_SLUG TestName`\\n2. **See it fail** — read the failure output\\n3. **Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}`** to understand what happened\\n4. **Implement the minimum code** to make it pass\\n5. **Run again** until it passes\\n6. **Write unit tests** to lock in the behavior\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter implementation:\\n1. Read the updated `implementer.md` to verify it's complete and clear\\n2. Run `/agent-integration:implement` mentally against a hypothetical agent to check the flow makes sense\\n3. Verify the E2E test progression is logical (each tier builds on the previous)\\n4. Ensure `/debug-e2e` is referenced at every failure point\\n5. Confirm unit tests are still written (just after E2E, not before)\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/f1da16a9-80ef-4161-b059-cf59cb1efc6b.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"887023ad-9e08-4ed8-b4fc-c1d9d5f8243a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:32:01.397Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: Update Agent Integration Skill to E2E-Driven TDD\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe agent integration skill currently uses unit-test-driven development in its implement phase (Phase 3). The user wants to flip this: **E2E tests become the primary spec**, and unit tests are written *after* each E